## When NOT to Use

<!-- WHY: Boundaries define quality. Explicitly name what this skill is NOT for. -->

- General-purpose advice (use a procedural or advisory skill instead)
- When the target is the creator's in-progress code AND independent review is needed
  (use an advisor agent — see `references/skill-vs-agent-discriminators.md §2` Q3 pollution)
- When the creator needs a second MIND in the room, not a frame on their thinking
  (use cognitive minds — `/create minds --cognitive`)
- When recall is rare (monthly or less) — this skill is too heavy to load on demand;
  use ambient_path_scoped delivery instead (`paths:` frontmatter)

