## Composability

<!-- WHY: Cognitive skills compose differently from procedural skills. -->
<!-- WHY: They are high-cost to load, so composition via skill-to-skill is rare. -->
<!-- WHY: Most composition happens via skills: frontmatter heredity on agents. -->

This cognitive skill is designed to compose via:

- **Agent heredity:** an agent spawned with this skill in its `skills:` frontmatter preloads
  the full 5-layer architecture into the fork. The agent then has access to this cognitive
  frame during its own task execution.
- **Path-scoped ambient activation:** if the skill declares `paths:` in frontmatter, it
  wakes itself when the creator touches a matching file — zero manual invocation needed.
- **Cross-skill reference:** procedural skills in the same domain can reference this skill
  by slug in their own references to suggest the cognitive frame when appropriate.

**Find related products:** [Browse cognitive skills on MyClaude](https://myclaude.sh/explore?category=skills&depth=cognitive)

